<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 04 at 1:38AM EST  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...Continued heavy rain will impact portions of DeKalb, south
central Forsyth, Gwinnett, northwestern Henry, central Fulton and
Clayton Counties through 230 AM EST...
At 137 AM EST, a line of heavy rain was over Chateau Elan, or 9
miles northwest of Winder, moving northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Heavy rain may cause temporary street flooding especially
in poor drainage areas.
Locations impacted include...
Atlanta, Lawrenceville, Decatur, Jonesboro, Sandy Springs, Roswell,
Johns Creek, Alpharetta, Dunwoody, East Point, Duluth, Forest Park,
Snellville, Suwanee, Riverdale, College Park, Lilburn, Loganville,
Chamblee and Norcross.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Motorists should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of
control due to hydroplaning.</instruction>
